The paper proposes a fairness-aware model for predicting demand for new mobility systems, which involves integrating various urban features and learning the spatial-temporal dynamics of a mobility system. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category, as well as the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories, which are relevant to the spatial and temporal aspects of the problem. Additionally, the paper introduces novel spatiotemporal fairness metrics, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the paper deals with transportation and urban mobility, which could make it relevant to the Computer-Aided Engineering (cs.CE) category.
